    • findBestSellerEvents

      @Query(nativeQuery=true, value="SELECT E.event_id, e.event_name, e.event_description, e.event_image, et.type_name, e.event_date,\n v.venue_id, v.venue_name,\n (subquery.total_tickets_sold / subquery.total_tickets) AS tickets_sold_ratio \nFROM (\n SELECT E.event_id,\n (\n SELECT SUM(CAST((s2.no_of_rows * s2.no_of_seats_per_row) AS DECIMAL))\n FROM dev.section s2\n WHERE s2.venue_id = E.venue_id\n ) AS total_tickets,\n COUNT(t.event_id) AS total_tickets_sold\n FROM dev.Event AS E\n LEFT JOIN dev.ticket t ON E.event_id = t.event_id\n RIGHT JOIN dev.section s ON E.venue_id = s.venue_id AND t.section_id = s.section_id\n WHERE E.review_status = \'approved\'\n AND E.deleted_at IS NULL\n GROUP BY E.event_id\n) AS subquery\nJOIN dev.Event AS E ON subquery.event_id = E.event_id \nJOIN dev.venue v ON E.venue_id = v.venue_id \nJOIN dev.event_type et ON e.type_id = et.type_id\nORDER BY tickets_sold_ratio DESC, subquery.total_tickets DESC LIMIT 7") List<Object[]> findBestSellerEvents()
